text: Kerstin Margareta "Kiki" Håkansson (23 July 1929 - 4 November 2024) was a Swedish model and beauty queen. She was the first winner of the Miss World beauty pageant after being crowned Miss Sweden World in 1951. She was born in Stockholm, Sweden. Håkansson died on 4 November 2024 in Washington at the age of 95.Kiki Hakansson, first Miss World passes away at 95 in California ==References== Category:1929 births Category:2024 deaths Category:Swedish models Category:People from Stockholm
